 \sum_{}^\infty [\sin(\frac{n\pi}{6})]^n  
\sum_{}^\infty [\sin(\frac{n\pi}{7})]^n 
\limsup_{n\rightarrow\infty} \left|\sin\left(\frac{n\pi}{6}\right)\right| = 1
\limsup_{n\rightarrow\infty} \left|\sin\left(\frac{n\pi}{7}\right)\right| < 1
\,n=3k\,\,,\,k\in\Bbb N\,\,,\,\,k\,\,\text{odd}
\sin\frac{n\pi}{6}=\sin\frac{k\pi}{2}=\pm 1\Longrightarrow \sin^n\frac{n\pi}{2}\rlap{\;\;\;\;\;/}\xrightarrow [n\to\infty]{}0
